WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:52.186 --> 00:00:53.999
[music]

00:00:55.527 --> 00:00:57.883
[Peter] All right guys.
Here we are, Pine Bluff.

00:00:57.950 --> 00:00:59.545
According to last census,

00:00:59.612 --> 00:01:03.530
America's fastest shrinking city.

00:01:03.597 --> 00:01:06.780
I believe it was a 12.5% decline.

00:01:09.830 --> 00:01:10.897
Empty streets.

00:01:11.638 --> 00:01:14.784
First impressions,
has a bit of an eerie feel to it.

00:01:15.209 --> 00:01:19.499
The population went from 2010 to 2020,

00:01:19.566 --> 00:01:23.450
from roughly 49,000 to 41,000.

00:01:23.517 --> 00:01:26.022
Now I believe it's around,
these are rough numbers,

00:01:26.089 --> 00:01:28.591
around 38,000.

00:01:28.658 --> 00:01:30.644
So declines like that,

00:01:30.711 --> 00:01:32.312
drastic declines,

00:01:32.379 --> 00:01:34.163
happen for a reason.

00:01:35.060 --> 00:01:37.044
And the goal of today is to

00:01:37.631 --> 00:01:39.099
meet some locals.

00:01:39.166 --> 00:01:41.931
Get their take on their city.
What's going on currently.

00:01:41.998 --> 00:01:44.035
What happened? Where are things going?

00:01:44.569 --> 00:01:46.040
Look at this old theater.

00:01:46.480 --> 00:01:48.421
You've got the ticket booth here.

00:01:48.510 --> 00:01:51.587
I'm sure in the '50s, and the '60s,
maybe the '70s,

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:54.249
this was just thriving.

00:01:55.222 --> 00:01:56.105
Listen to that.

00:01:56.172 --> 00:01:57.443
[flickering sound]

00:01:58.357 --> 00:02:00.220
These little plastic pieces.

00:02:00.287 --> 00:02:01.419
People coming up,

00:02:02.089 --> 00:02:03.441
"One ticket please."

00:02:04.122 --> 00:02:05.651
And you go to the matinee.

00:02:06.326 --> 00:02:08.842
See a movie
with your family and friends.

00:02:08.909 --> 00:02:09.962
Not long ago,

00:02:11.056 --> 00:02:14.713
noises of laughter
and children running around.

00:02:15.651 --> 00:02:19.279
And this is some
dangerous infrastructure for sure.

00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:21.526
Oh look at this beauty.

00:02:22.356 --> 00:02:23.786
This is built in style.

00:02:24.300 --> 00:02:26.446
When things were built with pride.

00:02:26.513 --> 00:02:28.678
When design was a concern.

00:02:31.251 --> 00:02:34.152
Here we have a place for sale by owner.

00:02:34.219 --> 00:02:36.101
This one's falling in on itself.

00:02:38.458 --> 00:02:41.157
I mean there's literally
nobody around you guys.

00:02:41.608 --> 00:02:44.282
We're gonna talk to
the first person we see.

00:02:44.349 --> 00:02:46.051
That's a beautiful mural though.

00:02:46.118 --> 00:02:47.300
University of Arkansas.

00:02:47.367 --> 00:02:50.602
There's a university I believe
on the side of this town.

00:02:51.204 --> 00:02:54.039
The only noises are electric boxes

00:02:54.106 --> 00:02:57.488
and the very occasional car going by.

00:03:03.745 --> 00:03:06.392
Vines taking over
the side of these buildings.

00:03:07.955 --> 00:03:11.842
So Pine Bluff has one of
the roughest reputations in Arkansas.

00:03:12.570 --> 00:03:15.255
Violent crime per 1,000 is around 16.

00:03:15.735 --> 00:03:18.319
National is around 4.

00:03:18.386 --> 00:03:20.066
So way over the national average.

00:03:20.133 --> 00:03:22.097
Homicides 2025,

00:03:22.798 --> 00:03:24.038
were 16.

00:03:24.464 --> 00:03:28.660
That's worse than New Orleans,
Baltimore, Detroit, per capita.

00:03:28.727 --> 00:03:31.248
So 41 per 100,000.

00:03:31.315 --> 00:03:33.323
And this year already has eight.

00:03:33.390 --> 00:03:36.043
So it's in a bit of a rough place

00:03:36.110 --> 00:03:37.826
from the statistics at least.

00:03:38.333 --> 00:03:40.978
But that's not the full story. Definitely.

00:03:41.045 --> 00:03:43.927
First impression,
there's no one down here to feel

00:03:44.482 --> 00:03:46.011
it's really any dangerous.

00:03:46.460 --> 00:03:47.981
And look at this beauty.

00:03:48.048 --> 00:03:50.481
It says Hood right above the entryway.

00:03:51.926 --> 00:03:53.119
This is interesting.

00:03:54.693 --> 00:03:57.470
"Like the proverbial monster
that destroyed its creator,

00:03:57.537 --> 00:04:01.219
government has become that which will
destroy the very rights and freedoms

00:04:01.286 --> 00:04:03.013
it was established to protect.

00:04:03.080 --> 00:04:06.485
We have the power to stop it though
without bloody violence.

00:04:06.990 --> 00:04:08.343
Okay we got a lot here.

00:04:08.860 --> 00:04:12.360
The only change by Democrats
and Republicans would be bigger government

00:04:12.427 --> 00:04:14.173
and more violation of our rights.

00:04:14.240 --> 00:04:16.979
There is an alternative.
This is the Libertarian Party.

00:04:17.046 --> 00:04:19.296
If you're for more freedom
and less government

00:04:19.363 --> 00:04:21.086
then you are indeed a Libertarian.

00:04:21.153 --> 00:04:24.329
Okay there we go.
We got some political operation here.

00:04:24.866 --> 00:04:25.749
Pine Bluff.

00:04:27.334 --> 00:04:30.870
I think this is the courthouse
or some government building.

00:04:31.620 --> 00:04:32.503
Excuse me, sir.

00:04:32.929 --> 00:04:35.390
-Is this courthouse still in operation?
-Yes.

00:04:35.457 --> 00:04:37.277
-Are you from Pine Bluff?
-Yes.

00:04:37.344 --> 00:04:38.802
What's it like right now?

00:04:38.869 --> 00:04:40.194
How are things?

00:04:40.261 --> 00:04:42.043
-The state of the city?
-Yeah.

00:04:42.110 --> 00:04:42.993
[scoffs]

00:04:43.451 --> 00:04:46.616
It's not all that great right now.
The economy is terrible.

00:04:46.683 --> 00:04:48.306
All the jobs are leaving.

00:04:48.373 --> 00:04:52.864
It just seems like it's a conspiracy
to make sure it stays this way.

00:04:52.931 --> 00:04:56.831
It's in somebody's best interest if
Pine Bluff stays in the shape that it's in.

00:04:56.898 --> 00:04:59.698
-You think so?
-I believe so. I've been here all my life.

00:04:59.765 --> 00:05:02.043
Other than my six years in the military.

00:05:02.110 --> 00:05:04.185
-Nice. Thank you, sir.
-I came right back.

00:05:04.252 --> 00:05:06.994
And anybody who wants to
move the city forward,

00:05:07.061 --> 00:05:08.757
they don't last long around here.

00:05:08.824 --> 00:05:09.707
-Okay.

00:05:09.774 --> 00:05:13.124
So what I'm seeing, I've literally
been here 15 minutes, first time.

00:05:13.526 --> 00:05:15.291
[man shouting in the distance]

00:05:15.382 --> 00:05:17.382
-What's that?
-[shouting continues]

00:05:20.654 --> 00:05:22.961
-No this man has dementia.
-Okay. Okay.

00:05:23.718 --> 00:05:25.918
-What's your name?
-My name is Anthony Royal.

00:05:25.985 --> 00:05:27.415
Anthony, Peter Santenello.

00:05:27.899 --> 00:05:31.471
Okay.
So I'm seeing beautiful old architecture.

00:05:31.538 --> 00:05:32.342
Mm-hmm.

00:05:32.409 --> 00:05:36.151
So when you were young was this place
thriving or what was it like?

00:05:36.218 --> 00:05:38.137
The entire downtown was full.

00:05:38.204 --> 00:05:41.626
We had businesses
always in operation, movie theaters.

00:05:41.693 --> 00:05:45.368
We had everything
that Little Rock or Memphis had.

00:05:45.879 --> 00:05:48.156
Little Rock and Pine Bluff
was neck and neck…

00:05:48.223 --> 00:05:49.341
-Seriously?
-Mm-hmm.

00:05:50.050 --> 00:05:52.598
Early '80s
we had close to 70,000 people here.

00:05:53.130 --> 00:05:57.607
Around the '90s, our industrial park
seemed like it started to close down.

00:05:57.674 --> 00:05:59.885
Businesses started to leave one by one.

00:05:59.952 --> 00:06:01.768
-So everyone was employed, working?

00:06:01.835 --> 00:06:04.927
Everybody was employed.
The city was moving forward.

00:06:04.994 --> 00:06:06.843
-It was a safe town back in the day?

00:06:06.910 --> 00:06:09.537
I believe so.
I mean you gon' have crime everywhere.

00:06:09.604 --> 00:06:12.712
If you consider the crime here
with the population that we had

00:06:12.779 --> 00:06:15.749
we're no different
than any other city in Arkansas.

00:06:15.816 --> 00:06:18.678
But it just seems to be
highlighted more so here.

00:06:18.745 --> 00:06:21.898
In my opinion
it's in someone's best interest

00:06:21.965 --> 00:06:24.959
for Pine Bluff to stay
in the state that it's in right now.

00:06:25.026 --> 00:06:28.804
Because every time we attempt to grow,
every time we take two steps forward,

00:06:28.871 --> 00:06:30.688
they knock us back four or five.

00:06:30.755 --> 00:06:33.941
We have so much corruption
within the city right now.

00:06:34.008 --> 00:06:36.503
-You feel okay saying that
working for the city?

00:06:36.570 --> 00:06:38.848
Well I work for the county.

00:06:38.915 --> 00:06:40.503
-Oh okay.
-[laughter]

00:06:40.570 --> 00:06:42.665
But we got it in the county too.

00:06:42.732 --> 00:06:44.903
So you're saying serious corruption here?

00:06:44.970 --> 00:06:47.956
Serious corruption
and nobody seems to do anything about it.

00:06:48.023 --> 00:06:49.435
We appealed to the governor,

00:06:49.502 --> 00:06:52.329
legislative offices at the capital.

00:06:52.706 --> 00:06:55.882
Let's help us corral
some of the stuff that's going on.

00:06:56.810 --> 00:06:59.978
-Why are you holding out?
You could move somewhere else.

00:07:00.045 --> 00:07:03.945
Well my main reason for being here
when I came back is I have children.

00:07:04.012 --> 00:07:07.880
Right now I just feel like I'm too old
to go anywhere. I'm almost 60.

00:07:08.310 --> 00:07:10.507
-It's your place? You grew up here?
-Yeah.

00:07:10.574 --> 00:07:12.894
It was a nice town. We had a nice mix.

00:07:13.501 --> 00:07:17.348
You know we were almost 50-50
Black, White population.

00:07:18.669 --> 00:07:20.630
Everyone got along pretty well?

00:07:20.697 --> 00:07:22.877
We never had any…

00:07:22.944 --> 00:07:24.003
-There was no beef?

00:07:25.498 --> 00:07:26.846
Not in my lifetime.

00:07:26.913 --> 00:07:29.983
-Once again, my opinion.
-You think it can come back?

00:07:30.050 --> 00:07:33.303
I believe it can
but we gotta clean the city.

00:07:33.370 --> 00:07:35.075
All right. Well you're part of it.

00:07:35.142 --> 00:07:37.163
You just mowed this lawn. It looks nice.

00:07:37.230 --> 00:07:38.937
Thank you. Thank you.

00:07:39.004 --> 00:07:41.157
I'm trying to edge now. Yes sir.

00:07:41.690 --> 00:07:42.573
-Take care.

00:07:43.720 --> 00:07:46.458
So I've only been in Arkansas
for a couple days.

00:07:46.525 --> 00:07:49.921
But that's what it's like
as far as friendliness.

00:07:49.988 --> 00:07:52.687
Everyone is super friendly

00:07:53.173 --> 00:07:54.776
and willing to share.

00:07:54.843 --> 00:07:57.784
And when you're making videos
that's what you want.

00:07:58.511 --> 00:07:59.499
[train passes]

00:08:07.264 --> 00:08:10.796
So the economy here in the early 1800s,

00:08:11.316 --> 00:08:13.561
cotton, like so much of this region.

00:08:14.132 --> 00:08:17.276
Railroad came in 1873.

00:08:17.343 --> 00:08:21.925
End of the 1800s,
river commerce brought in industry.

00:08:21.992 --> 00:08:24.970
The lumber, the timber industry flourished.

00:08:25.448 --> 00:08:29.234
And then I read
there was a big flood, 1927.

00:08:29.706 --> 00:08:32.178
And that really knocked the place down.

00:08:32.245 --> 00:08:35.557
And then as the man said,
the industry went away.

00:08:35.971 --> 00:08:39.085
People left, unemployment rose, crime rose.

00:08:39.526 --> 00:08:43.289
I mean there might be someone
still living in there. Who knows?

00:08:43.356 --> 00:08:47.062
If you're homeless there are
a lot of vacant places for shelter.

00:08:49.163 --> 00:08:51.989
This place has
a post-apocalyptic feel to it.

00:08:52.916 --> 00:08:54.034
At least down here.

00:08:55.036 --> 00:08:57.918
Look at the nature
just coming right back through.

00:08:58.373 --> 00:09:00.311
Nature always wins in the end.

00:09:00.750 --> 00:09:02.750
And if this stays like this

00:09:02.817 --> 00:09:05.279
the next hundred or so years,

00:09:05.346 --> 00:09:09.987
well, there'll be no building left
and it'll just be trees, forests.

00:09:12.541 --> 00:09:15.929
This is the opposite of gentrification.

00:09:22.295 --> 00:09:26.541
What will Pine Bluff look like
in 10, 20, 30 years?

00:09:26.615 --> 00:09:28.850
That's why I love making these videos.

00:09:28.917 --> 00:09:33.384
Because the goal is
this is still online in 10, 20, 30 years.

00:09:34.091 --> 00:09:38.314
And you can look back at
what society and places were like.

00:09:39.630 --> 00:09:41.310
Sort of a pause

00:09:42.243 --> 00:09:44.469
on 2026

00:09:45.136 --> 00:09:46.243
to go back to.

00:09:47.595 --> 00:09:49.489
Here we go. Here's some oxygen.

00:09:49.556 --> 00:09:51.085
We have some artists here.

00:09:51.658 --> 00:09:53.958
Across the street, a new playground.

00:09:54.461 --> 00:09:56.186
Let me put the feeling on here.

00:09:56.655 --> 00:09:58.622
It is a bit of Gary, Indiana.

00:09:59.579 --> 00:10:00.991
It's a bit of the South.

00:10:01.468 --> 00:10:03.163
It's a bit of the Rust Belt.

00:10:03.230 --> 00:10:06.239
It's like a nuclear bomb went off

00:10:06.306 --> 00:10:08.423
and everyone evacuated pretty much.

00:10:09.003 --> 00:10:10.827
Except for a few cars going by.

00:10:15.001 --> 00:10:16.590
-You guys are locals here?
-Yes.

00:10:16.657 --> 00:10:20.019
-How are things these days?
-Everybody's trying to live and survive.

00:10:20.086 --> 00:10:22.968
But to keep a positive mindset
we will say growth.

00:10:23.443 --> 00:10:25.183
-It's growing?
-It's growing a lot.

00:10:25.250 --> 00:10:30.043
You come look 10 years ago,
it was nowhere near this.

00:10:30.110 --> 00:10:34.386
Half the buildings
that were torn down were still up.

00:10:34.694 --> 00:10:36.313
Like the ones that are still up.

00:10:36.380 --> 00:10:38.705
So there were buildings
that were too far gone?

00:10:38.772 --> 00:10:39.833
-Yeah.
-Okay.

00:10:39.900 --> 00:10:42.950
I was trying to get into this barber shop
but it's closed huh?

00:10:43.017 --> 00:10:44.672
-No, it's open.
-It's open?

00:10:44.739 --> 00:10:46.960
-Is this your guy's shop?
-My brother's.

00:10:47.027 --> 00:10:50.249
Okay. I like to show off
businesses that are happening.

00:10:51.230 --> 00:10:52.465
[Peter] Look at this.

00:10:53.243 --> 00:10:54.596
Nice little oasis here.

00:10:55.707 --> 00:10:56.590
This is great.

00:11:00.460 --> 00:11:03.025
I noticed a new playground down there.

00:11:03.092 --> 00:11:06.003
-So there's some energy coming back in?
-Yeah.

00:11:06.070 --> 00:11:09.132
We see a lot of the negative
that comes through Pine Bluff

00:11:09.199 --> 00:11:14.542
and we try to put a lot of small things
to indicate the positive

00:11:14.609 --> 00:11:17.325
because I mean that's all we got now.

00:11:17.392 --> 00:11:20.071
We're already a smaller community.

00:11:20.138 --> 00:11:21.973
We have to work with what we have.

00:11:22.476 --> 00:11:25.149
-And we gotta be thankful.
-Exactly.

00:11:25.216 --> 00:11:26.924
You know what I'm saying?

00:11:26.991 --> 00:11:31.089
I think right now everybody just
needs to be grateful for what they have.

00:11:31.156 --> 00:11:34.126
And if somebody's trying to
build back up Pine Bluff,

00:11:34.193 --> 00:11:36.267
then you know that the dream is not lost.

00:11:36.334 --> 00:11:37.709
-Okay. Yeah.

00:11:37.776 --> 00:11:39.429
So we are the younger generation,

00:11:39.496 --> 00:11:41.766
the generation after us,
we're still dreaming.

00:11:41.833 --> 00:11:46.303
So we're just happy to see that
there is some type of progress going on.

00:11:46.370 --> 00:11:47.405
-Okay. Yeah.

00:11:47.472 --> 00:11:49.917
Everything always goes in a cycle, right?

00:11:49.984 --> 00:11:54.079
And those guys that were here in '60s,
they were on the top of the cycle.

00:11:54.146 --> 00:11:56.314
And then it went down
and then where are we?

00:11:56.381 --> 00:11:57.825
I mean every town has this.

00:11:57.892 --> 00:12:01.535
Is it hit the bottom
and it's coming back or it's who knows?

00:12:01.616 --> 00:12:04.210
I say we scraped the bottom.
Didn't touch it.

00:12:04.277 --> 00:12:05.756
You didn't touch it? Okay.

00:12:05.823 --> 00:12:07.342
It's definitely coming back.

00:12:07.409 --> 00:12:09.949
-Okay. But guys like you
are staying in town.

00:12:10.016 --> 00:12:11.842
Young guys what are you in your 20s?

00:12:11.909 --> 00:12:13.632
Yeah. I'm 23.

00:12:13.699 --> 00:12:15.449
-25.
-Cool. You don't want to leave?

00:12:15.516 --> 00:12:19.540
I don't. I mean it's gonna be
a point in time where you have to…

00:12:19.607 --> 00:12:23.000
Of course there's other things in life,
opportunities, growth.

00:12:23.067 --> 00:12:25.443
But for the time being,

00:12:25.510 --> 00:12:28.662
there's no one that's gonna
get to the youth like the youth.

00:12:28.729 --> 00:12:31.949
We're the closest to them
when it comes to teenagers.

00:12:32.550 --> 00:12:35.253
-Yeah. You guys have an important role.

00:12:35.320 --> 00:12:36.607
Yes. Most definitely.

00:12:36.674 --> 00:12:38.990
I try my best to be around the kids.

00:12:39.057 --> 00:12:40.807
Especially when it comes to sports.

00:12:40.874 --> 00:12:44.172
When it comes to just being there
as an advocate, a mentor.

00:12:44.239 --> 00:12:46.089
A lot of the kids need that nowadays.

00:12:46.156 --> 00:12:48.434
And to piggyback on what he's saying,

00:12:48.501 --> 00:12:53.354
for them to see a change come in here
and see people trying to do things,

00:12:53.421 --> 00:12:54.988
it kinda motivate them.

00:12:55.055 --> 00:12:57.305
Even on the lost dreams
it kinda motivate them

00:12:57.372 --> 00:12:59.751
to pick it back up and just try.

00:12:59.818 --> 00:13:00.701
-Yeah.

00:13:00.774 --> 00:13:02.778
Long as you trying to keep going,

00:13:02.845 --> 00:13:05.268
you got to look at it
from a positive angle.

00:13:05.335 --> 00:13:08.893
-Look we have social media these days.
It's grabbing attention.

00:13:08.960 --> 00:13:12.110
People need real,
in the flesh, positive role models.

00:13:12.177 --> 00:13:13.678
-Real life time.
-Yeah.

00:13:13.745 --> 00:13:14.804
That's exactly it.

00:13:17.260 --> 00:13:18.539
Look at this beauty.

00:13:18.606 --> 00:13:21.313
The Hotel Pines constructed in 1912.

00:13:21.380 --> 00:13:22.512
It was considered

00:13:22.579 --> 00:13:26.439
one of Arkansas's showcase hotels.

00:13:26.506 --> 00:13:29.369
Saw the traders, the business people,

00:13:29.924 --> 00:13:31.432
coming to downtown here.

00:13:31.499 --> 00:13:33.359
Stay at the Hotel Pines.

00:13:33.426 --> 00:13:35.793
I'm sure there was
amazing ballroom in there.

00:13:35.860 --> 00:13:37.066
Excellent food.

00:13:37.520 --> 00:13:38.913
Ornate detail.

00:13:38.980 --> 00:13:40.203
The marble floors.

00:13:40.816 --> 00:13:43.345
And then one day the people stopped coming.

00:13:44.563 --> 00:13:46.349
So this is an interesting corner.

00:13:46.416 --> 00:13:48.678
We have this beautiful building.

00:13:48.745 --> 00:13:51.461
Old pharmacy. Shoe shop.
Let's check that out.

00:13:51.948 --> 00:13:54.413
And then you have Siemens Bank.

00:13:54.480 --> 00:13:55.951
Tallest building in town.

00:13:56.678 --> 00:13:58.437
And then The Generator.

00:13:58.504 --> 00:14:03.085
"An innovation hub
powered by Go Forward Pine Bluff."

00:14:03.576 --> 00:14:06.308
They're trying here.
You can tell. New sidewalk.

00:14:06.760 --> 00:14:07.887
Innovation hub.

00:14:09.120 --> 00:14:11.179
Let's check out what they're doing.

00:14:13.063 --> 00:14:13.946
Who's here?

00:14:16.968 --> 00:14:18.648
How you doing? What's your name?

00:14:18.715 --> 00:14:21.327
-Grace.
-Okay. What's going on here, Grace?

00:14:21.394 --> 00:14:24.529
We do like a lot of different
classes for small businesses.

00:14:24.596 --> 00:14:27.078
And then sometimes
we do like education purposes

00:14:27.145 --> 00:14:28.965
like partner with different schools.

00:14:29.032 --> 00:14:31.021
We have the youth program for kids.

00:14:31.088 --> 00:14:35.813
And then we just had a session
that helped elderly people with illiteracy.

00:14:35.880 --> 00:14:37.247
But you just missed them.

00:14:37.314 --> 00:14:39.260
It would have been cool if came.

00:14:39.327 --> 00:14:41.323
-They just left?
-Yeah.

00:14:41.390 --> 00:14:44.633
Like probably like 30 minutes ago.
Well I'd say 20 minutes ago.

00:14:44.700 --> 00:14:46.378
-So you're from Pine Bluff?
-Yeah.

00:14:46.445 --> 00:14:48.426
Do you love it? What's your take on it?

00:14:48.493 --> 00:14:49.913
It's nice. It's home.

00:14:49.980 --> 00:14:53.141
Of course obviously I do want
to see it progress and get better.

00:14:53.208 --> 00:14:55.700
But I mean I like the people here.

00:14:56.174 --> 00:14:59.319
I love that some of them have the heart
to try to make the city better.

00:14:59.386 --> 00:15:00.878
-Like Pops.
-Yeah.

00:15:00.945 --> 00:15:03.195
You see how he's trying to
help the community?

00:15:03.262 --> 00:15:06.209
I like that we do have people here
like Ms. Kanisha.

00:15:06.276 --> 00:15:10.288
I don't know if you ever met her or not.
But she started a micro school out here.

00:15:10.355 --> 00:15:12.387
I thought it was the coolest thing ever.

00:15:12.454 --> 00:15:15.472
She has a passion for education.
So I thought that was cool.

00:15:15.546 --> 00:15:17.682
-Okay. So you think you're gonna stay?

00:15:18.123 --> 00:15:20.163
Um… Probably not.

00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:22.753
Because I mean
once I finish school and everything

00:15:22.820 --> 00:15:25.582
I do want to venture out and explore.

00:15:25.985 --> 00:15:29.061
But I mean
I really want to be able to hopefully

00:15:29.128 --> 00:15:32.040
be in a time of life
where I can give back to my community.

00:15:32.107 --> 00:15:35.424
But I do want to leave
and go to different countries and stuff.

00:15:40.943 --> 00:15:42.066
God's Hospital.

00:15:44.078 --> 00:15:45.292
Henry Marx Company

00:15:45.816 --> 00:15:47.292
Best Clothes in Town

00:15:48.505 --> 00:15:49.562
Shoe Express.

00:15:55.010 --> 00:15:57.868
I feel like this is how it was

00:15:58.515 --> 00:16:00.121
57 years ago.

00:16:00.188 --> 00:16:01.435
Like exactly.

00:16:01.502 --> 00:16:03.012
[whistling]

00:16:03.563 --> 00:16:06.104
-You just had this fixed up, your purse?
-Yes.

00:16:06.171 --> 00:16:08.806
He had fixed it up once.
Now he's fixed it up again.

00:16:08.873 --> 00:16:10.193
You thought I had a gun?

00:16:10.260 --> 00:16:14.157
Yeah. When you were coming down there
it looked like a gun.

00:16:14.224 --> 00:16:16.265
I said surely he's not doing nothing.

00:16:16.332 --> 00:16:19.782
Then you came in here
I could tell it was something different.

00:16:19.849 --> 00:16:21.243
-It was a GoPro. Yeah.

00:16:21.310 --> 00:16:24.087
I guess with the stick
it looks like a gun a little bit.

00:16:24.154 --> 00:16:25.319
[man] It's $22.15.

00:16:26.352 --> 00:16:28.146
-I'm Peter.
-I'm Mary, how are you?

00:16:28.213 --> 00:16:30.277
Mary. Great to meet you ma'am.

00:16:30.344 --> 00:16:31.227
Santenello.

00:16:31.804 --> 00:16:33.174
-What is that?
-Italian.

00:16:33.241 --> 00:16:34.124
-Italian?
-Yeah.

00:16:35.546 --> 00:16:38.130
The guy that taught me shoe repair
was Italian.

00:16:38.197 --> 00:16:40.006
I learnt this trade through him.

00:16:40.073 --> 00:16:41.046
Junior high school.

00:16:41.113 --> 00:16:44.013
-The Italian guy?
-That's the guy. Dave Lupo.

00:16:44.080 --> 00:16:46.304
And maybe you'll pass it on
to someone else?

00:16:46.371 --> 00:16:47.303
-I pray I do.

00:16:47.370 --> 00:16:49.508
This art right here is just well needed.

00:16:50.142 --> 00:16:51.204
People still need it.

00:16:51.580 --> 00:16:55.144
This used to be a men's store.
A high dollar men's store.

00:16:55.211 --> 00:16:57.684
If you wanted a nice suit, tie, shirt.

00:16:57.751 --> 00:16:59.968
-And it still is?  Get a suit.
-Yeah.

00:17:00.035 --> 00:17:03.437
I don't care as much as the guy
that Henry and Marx used to carry

00:17:03.504 --> 00:17:04.884
or Mark Bell.

00:17:04.951 --> 00:17:07.090
I just brought in a few things to wear as

00:17:07.157 --> 00:17:10.757
sometimes people just want to
buy in store instead of online.

00:17:10.824 --> 00:17:13.028
-Yeah? Try it on?
-Try it on.

00:17:13.095 --> 00:17:16.930
See what you like and if it's not
the size you want I can always order it.

00:17:16.997 --> 00:17:20.103
A lot of people that's what they do.
Come on I'll show you my shop.

00:17:20.170 --> 00:17:22.839
My main goal is fixing shoes.

00:17:23.310 --> 00:17:25.143
That's an art form. Oh yeah.

00:17:25.210 --> 00:17:27.379
I put soles and heels in boots.

00:17:27.446 --> 00:17:29.229
-This is classic huh? This machine?

00:17:29.296 --> 00:17:32.083
This machine was built in the early '60s.

00:17:32.603 --> 00:17:34.847
-It must weigh a ton.
-Oh, it does.

00:17:35.290 --> 00:17:36.893
[machine clacks and whirrs]

00:17:38.010 --> 00:17:40.003
Put the boot on here, sews it up.

00:17:42.378 --> 00:17:43.790
Sews your sole back on.

00:17:44.530 --> 00:17:45.946
Another machine here.

00:17:47.270 --> 00:17:48.858
[machine whirrs and clacks]

00:17:49.980 --> 00:17:53.457
And what that does is
it sews your sole back on your shoes.

00:17:53.524 --> 00:17:55.503
This machine right here is a sander.

00:17:55.570 --> 00:17:57.173
Put a new sole on here.

00:17:57.240 --> 00:17:58.440
[machine whirrs]

00:18:08.146 --> 00:18:09.205
-You like doing it?

00:18:09.793 --> 00:18:10.676
Love it.

00:18:12.130 --> 00:18:15.978
I grew up here and so that's when
things were really flourishing downtown

00:18:16.045 --> 00:18:19.614
but over the years
I saw it just kind of dwindle down.

00:18:20.460 --> 00:18:22.271
And I blame it on Walmart

00:18:22.338 --> 00:18:25.141
because when Walmart was at the mall

00:18:25.661 --> 00:18:27.837
it was flourishing
and everything was going.

00:18:27.904 --> 00:18:32.365
And then they moved to one central location
which was out by the freeway.

00:18:32.432 --> 00:18:34.033
It drew all the businesses out.

00:18:34.100 --> 00:18:36.038
It sucked out the businesses.

00:18:36.600 --> 00:18:38.186
But we're coming back.

00:18:38.253 --> 00:18:40.678
There's a lot of traffic
always flowing downtown.

00:18:40.745 --> 00:18:41.712
It's coming back.

00:18:42.860 --> 00:18:43.989
[siren blaring]

00:18:46.120 --> 00:18:49.388
You can see how we started
way down there at the end of the street

00:18:49.455 --> 00:18:50.635
there at the courthouse

00:18:50.702 --> 00:18:52.261
came all the way up Main Street

00:18:52.328 --> 00:18:55.908
